start.label: don't count your chickens before they're hatched

examples.en: When exactly did the incident occur?
Nothing occurred that seemed important.
New ideas occur to him in the act of writing.
It did not occur to me to mention it.
Many suicides occur in prisons.
Marble also occurs here.
The disease occurs chiefly in tropical climates.
It occurred to me that we should hire another secretary.
The event is scheduled to occur at noon tomorrow.
The explosion occurred at 5.30 a.m.
She forecast that an earthquake would occur.
Most infections occur in childhood.
It is uncertain how likely this is to occur.
No one was ready for what was about to occur.
There's a chance that a similar event will occur in the future.
The realization that a catastrophe could occur at any time sobered them up.
The plant occurs naturally throughout South America.
Flight delays do occur, for reasons that are outside our control.
Some mangles in newspaper articles occur under the pressure of deadlines.
A third of accidental deaths occur in the home.
Problems only occur when this attitude is taken to extremes.
The highest rates of unemployment occur in the inner urban areas.
Combustion may occur at high temperatures.
Few continental rises occur in the Pacific Ocean.
The Rocky Mountains occur occasionally in collateral ridges.
Although arbitrary arrests are illegal, they continue to occur in many parts of the country.
Whooping cough occurs mainly in young children.
Precious stones occur in a large area in Brazil.
Retrenchment may occur within an industry when there are shifts in market share.
The major term of a syllogism must occur twice.
